View details and comments show up when the mouse hovers over the entire comment item.
± icons are in color, to make the commit type immediately obvious
Existing comments are always displayed, unless the list exceeds a certain amount (like 10), where the most recent would be shown and there would be a view all link.
Clicking in the “Add a comment…” box expands the comment entry, exactly as if one clicked the comment action above.
There is obvious hover feedback for links. (Color subject to change)
Clicking on a folder will open the folder. Clicking on a file will open the file.
Multiple sparkles (commits) are collapsed, with a view all link available, and time ago is from start to finish of the sparkles.
Directories are truncated to the relevant information. Successive directory listings will be shortened as well. Hovering over the directories will show the entire path.
Dates are shown only on change of day. Today and Yesterday are shown with friendly names.
